Former Senator and 2023 Kaduna Gubernatorial aspirant, Shehu Sani, has urged the Hajj Commission to sentence Nigerians displaying campaign posters in Mecca. The former lawmaker disclosed this on Sunday via his Twitter page, expressing that the Nigerians are not there for religious purposes. He wrote, “Those displaying or pasting Nigerian Political Campaign posters in Mecca are not there for religious purposes. “The Hajj Commission should take note of the culprits and ban them for Ten years.”